  <body>
    <header>
      Optimized YZ-Plane
    </header>
    <div id="contents">
      <section>
        <h1>Explanation</h1>
        <p>
          The member function <code>find_all_hits</code> looks for <em>all</em> hits between a primitive and a ray.
          However, it is often the case that only the first positive hit is necessary. It is therefore
          more efficient to also implement a member function that specializes in finding this first positive hit.
        </p>
        <aside class="boxed2">
          <h1>Task</h1>
          <p>
            Override YZ-plane's <code>find_first_positive_hit</code>.
          </p>
        </aside>
      </section>
    </div>
  </body>

